<br>
Antonica:<br>
A - Troll SK/Shaman in Rathe (never camped, easy, ok loot)<br>
B - HG's in Rathe (always camped, kind of tough, mad loot)<br>
C - Spectre in Feerott (frequently camped, easy, good loot)<br>
D - Wandering Bouncers in Feerott (never camped as they wander, easy to kill but you have to cross the river every 10 minutes, drop Crude Steins seldom, always FS weapon).<br>
E - Guk if you can find a few people<br>
F - Qeynos Catacombs (if you don't mind WK run as much as I do)<br>
<br>
Faydwer:<br>
A - Happ (easy, watch out for mean horsey, nuke sort of hurts)<br>
B - Brownie scouts with an air pet. And they come to you!! (payback for level 12)<br>
C - Kedge 2nd floor (always quiet and boring)<br>
D - MM for moonlight farming (if elven smithing is important to you)<br>
<br>
Kunark: <br>
A - Solo along castle wall in DL (and a ranger will grab 1 of every 3 of your pulls and then call you a n00b)<br>
B - BW bees (fun, but can easily turn ugly)<br>
C - Karnors (with group and see above concerning ugly))<br>
D - Glacier Yeti (never done these, but the tundra type got me from 39 to 44)<br>
E - Bloodgills in LOIO (but after 46 when death isn't absurd penalty. These take a few tries to get the hang of the process)<br>
<br>
Velious: <br>
IC, EW, GD all have places a 44-49 mage and Jabober can solo stuff. <br>
<br>
I am thoroughly anti-social and feel as though druids already gripe enough, so I never port. Hence, I always try to maximize my camp search time by grouping them like this. As always, your mileage will vary.<br>
<br>
BTW - I am a seriously below average mage (142 INT at 47, less than 50 in all unbuffed resists) in the gear department and have soloed effectively in all the above spots (except the dungeons) with few deaths. So if I can do it, any regular, well-equipped magician can too.<br>
<br>
Aan<br>
